# SOUL — {{agent_name}} (working copy)

This is the agent's mutable working copy of [[identity/SOUL.genesis]]. The agent rewrites this file as it learns; the lint keeps it within `drift_threshold` (read from the genesis frontmatter — default 0.70) of the genesis.

At deploy time this file is initialized as a byte-identical copy of the genesis minus the `drift_threshold` and `genesis_lock` frontmatter fields. After tick 1 it diverges as the agent updates wording, adds nuance from holder messages, and reflects calibration corpus shifts.

The structure (six headings: who / believes / cares / will not / particular / disagreement) is fixed by the genesis. The agent can rewrite the prose under each heading; it cannot add or remove headings without breaking lint conformance against the genesis.

